## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-102">Ciò `enum` specifica il tipo di evento quando viene generato un evento per un <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-102">This `enum` specifies the event type when an event is raised for an <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-103">Tutte le operazioni che modificano l'albero XML suddividere a una serie di tipi primitivi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-103">All operations that modify the XML tree break down to a series of primitives.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-104">Esistono quattro tipi di primitive.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-104">There are four types of primitives.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-105">Due le primitive (Aggiungi e Rimuovi) di agire su raccolte.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-105">Two of the primitives (Add and Remove) act on collections.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-106">Due di essi (nome e valore) agire su istanze.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-106">Two of them (Name and Value) act on instances.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-107">È un evento corrispondente per ciascuno di questi tipi primitivi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-107">There is a corresponding event for each of these primitives.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-108">È necessario prestare attenzione quando si modifica un albero XML all'interno di uno di questi eventi, perché ciò potrebbe provocare risultati imprevisti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-108">You should be careful when modifying an XML tree within one of these events, because doing this might lead to unexpected results.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-109">Ad esempio, se si riceve un <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changing> evento e durante l'elaborazione dell'evento viene rimosso il nodo dall'albero, si potrebbe non ricevere le <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changed> evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-109">For example, if you receive a <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changing> event, and while the event is being processed you remove the node from the tree, you might not receive the <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changed> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-110">Durante l'elaborazione di un evento, è possibile modificare un albero XML diverso da quello che contiene il nodo che riceve l'evento; è anche possibile modificare la stessa struttura, purché le modifiche non influiscono sui nodi specifici in cui è stato generato l'evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-110">When an event is being processed, it is valid to modify an XML tree other than the one that contains the node that is receiving the event; it is even valid to modify the same tree provided the modifications do not affect the specific nodes on which the event was raised.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-111">Tuttavia, se si modifica l'area dell'albero che contiene il nodo che riceve l'evento, gli eventi che ricevono e l'impatto per la struttura ad albero sono definiti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-111">However, if you modify the area of the tree that contains the node receiving the event, the events that you receive and the impact to the tree are undefined.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-112">Nell'esempio seguente genera un evento mediante l'aggiunta di un elemento all'albero.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-112">The following example raises an event by adding an element to the tree.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root", "content");  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Add(new XElement("Child", "child content"));  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-113">Questo esempio produce il seguente output:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-113">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changing: Add  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changed: Add  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-114">Nell'esempio seguente genera un evento tramite la rimozione di un elemento nell'albero.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-114">The following example raises an event by removing an element from the tree.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root",  
    new XElement("Child", "content")  
);  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Element("Child").Remove();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-115">Questo esempio produce il seguente output:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-115">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changing: Remove  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changed: Remove  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-116">Nell'esempio seguente genera un evento modificando il nome di un elemento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-116">The following example raises an event by changing the name of an element.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root", "content");  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Name = "NewName";  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-117">Questo esempio produce il seguente output:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-117">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changing: Name  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changed: Name  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-118">Nell'esempio seguente genera un evento, impostando il valore di un attributo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-118">The following example raises an event by setting the value of an attribute.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root",  
    new XAttribute("Att", "att value")  
);  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.FirstAttribute.Value = "new contents";  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0d5ab-119">Questo esempio produce il seguente output:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0d5ab-119">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XAttribute  
  Changing: Value  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XAttribute  
  Changed: Value  
```
